174
00:12:54.482 --> 00:12:56.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll leave in thirty minutes.

175
00:12:58.652 --> 00:13:00.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He’s hardly had any sleep.</i>

176
00:13:01.071 --> 00:13:03.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He’s gonna make himself sick.</i>

177
00:13:03.866 --> 00:13:08.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But…</i>
<i>I do envy him for having so much work.</i>

178
00:13:08.954 --> 00:13:10.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>In fact, it’s frustrating.</i>

179
00:13:11.540 --> 00:13:13.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You could stay in bed longer.

180
00:13:13.709 --> 00:13:16.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you try living like me,
you’ll die young.

181
00:13:16.712 --> 00:13:18.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I have to go to work.

182
00:13:20.758 --> 00:13:23.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The moving company Nobu works at
is short of staff,

183
00:13:23.844 --> 00:13:25.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so he introduced me
and got me a job there.

184
00:13:25.346 --> 00:13:28.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A moving company? That’s a manly job.

185
00:13:30.142 --> 00:13:34.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can no longer work in the evenings
with our band practicing every night,

186
00:13:34.188 --> 00:13:36.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I need to make my earnings
during the day.

187
00:13:37.024 --> 00:13:40.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's going on with your debut?
Any progress?

188
00:13:40.361 --> 00:13:41.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not really.

189
00:13:45.658 --> 00:13:50.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Back then, I stayed at Ren’s place</i>
<i>for about half of the week,</i>

190
00:13:50.871 --> 00:13:52.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but we missed each other often</i>

191
00:13:52.998 --> 00:13:55.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and would only see each other</i>
<i>for short periods.</i>

192
00:13:58.128 --> 00:13:59.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>When we were together,</i>

193
00:13:59.588 --> 00:14:02.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>we couldn’t control our passion</i>
<i>for each other,</i>

194
00:14:02.341 --> 00:14:05.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>so we hardly spent any time</i>
<i>talking about ourselves.</i>

195
00:14:09.181 --> 00:14:12.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But I thought it was better that way</i>

196
00:14:13.477 --> 00:14:15.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>because that way we could avoid</i>
<i>unnecessary subjects</i>

197
00:14:15.854 --> 00:14:17.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>that would only make us feel awkward.</i>

198
00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:35.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? Still there?

199
00:14:35.416 --> 00:14:37.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So annoying, aren’t they?

200
00:14:37.334 --> 00:14:39.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe I should move.
But maybe that won’t make any difference.

201
00:14:40.045 --> 00:14:41.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? What? Those papa-rakkyos?

202
00:14:41.797 --> 00:14:44.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not the rakkyos!
I’m talking about that woman!

203
00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:46.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I told you to have her go home!

204
00:14:46.927 --> 00:14:49.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rakkyo makes me wanna eat curry and rice.

205
00:14:49.471 --> 00:14:52.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah? I prefer Fukujinzuke
on my curry rice.

206
00:14:52.641 --> 00:14:55.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What? Curry rice wouldn’t be complete
without a raw egg.

207
00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:56.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right, Takumi?

208
00:14:56.645 --> 00:14:59.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t eat the common folk’s food!

209
00:14:59.148 --> 00:15:00.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
BEEF CURRY

210
00:15:00.232 --> 00:15:03.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Open a pack of curry,
and heat it in a pot.

211
00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:06.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When you find you’re running short,
add a pack at a time.

212
00:15:06.947 --> 00:15:09.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Be careful so that it doesn’t burn
and stick to the pot.

213
00:15:11.744 --> 00:15:14.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The rice is already cooked,

214
00:15:14.830 --> 00:15:17.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so place a little on each plate…

215
00:15:20.377 --> 00:15:21.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Komatsu?

216
00:15:24.256 --> 00:15:26.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
SERVICE AND GOODS ENTRANCE

217
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:28.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m very sorry.

218
00:15:28.761 --> 00:15:32.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It can’t be helped.
You’re not feeling well.

219
00:15:32.431 --> 00:15:34.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank goodness it happened
before we let the customers in.

220
00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:36.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am really sorry.

221
00:15:36.268 --> 00:15:38.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mustn’t take
summer heat fatigue lightly.

222
00:15:38.729 --> 00:15:41.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’d better go see a doctor.

223
00:15:43.442 --> 00:15:44.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

224
00:16:26.235 --> 00:16:30.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
PHARMACY

225
00:16:46.422 --> 00:16:49.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re eating it.
And at an employees’ cafeteria.

226
00:16:49.842 --> 00:16:52.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
THE COMMON FOLK’S CURRY RICE

227
00:16:52.594 --> 00:16:55.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These things are usually
the furthest from my mind,

228
00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:56.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so why is it that
when I suddenly remember it,

229
00:16:56.849 --> 00:16:58.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suddenly crave it?

230
00:16:59.643 --> 00:17:02.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bottom line is, you love the stuff?

231
00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:22.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I wish it would end already.
-What?

232
00:17:23.876 --> 00:17:25.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Summer vacation.

233
00:17:28.881 --> 00:17:30.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Only three more days.

234
00:17:30.632 --> 00:17:33.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Summer vacation seems like
a long break, but it goes by so fast.

235
00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:37.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If at least discussions
about your debut were more concrete,

236
00:17:37.806 --> 00:17:39.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could go home feeling relieved.

237
00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:40.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
WORLD HISTORY, JAPANESE HISTORY,
BIOLOGY, SCIENCE, MATH

238
00:17:40.684 --> 00:17:42.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s been a month already
since you signed that contract,

239
00:17:42.770 --> 00:17:45.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you don't even have an agency yet.

240
00:17:45.981 --> 00:17:48.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
