of that temporary contract.

242
00:17:53.113 --> 00:17:55.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How is it different
from the official contract?

243
00:17:55.991 --> 00:17:58.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d say it’s something like
an engagement before a wedding?

244
00:17:59.953 --> 00:18:03.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Kawano is presently working hard
to collect funds and personnel

245
00:18:03.832 --> 00:18:08.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to organize a big reception for us.

246
00:18:09.546 --> 00:18:12.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The contract is there
so we remain faithful to them,

247
00:18:12.633 --> 00:18:14.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
even if others approach us.

248
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:19.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In turn, we’re free to use
Gaia’s music studios as much as we want

249
00:18:19.848 --> 00:18:22.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
while we prepare to be beautiful brides.

250
00:18:22.392 --> 00:18:23.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I get it!

251
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:27.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I finally understand now. Thank you.

252
00:18:27.523 --> 00:18:31.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Misato. You’re older than me,
so why do you talk so politely to me?

253
00:18:34.363 --> 00:18:36.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, you’re younger than me, Shin,

254
00:18:37.074 --> 00:18:40.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so how come you’re able to help me
with my 12th grade homework?

255
00:18:40.452 --> 00:18:42.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can only help you with your English.

256
00:18:42.955 --> 00:18:45.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have Yasu or someone help you
with the other stuff.

257
00:18:45.249 --> 00:18:47.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I knew it!
-You knew it?

258
00:18:47.584 --> 00:18:50.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have that pretty and luminous face
because you’re only half-Japanese, right?

259
00:18:50.587 --> 00:18:52.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pretty and luminous?

260
00:18:52.589 --> 00:18:54.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can hide it all you want,
but I can tell.

261
00:18:54.883 --> 00:18:56.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s why your English is so good, right?

262
00:18:58.220 --> 00:19:01.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My English is good
because I was raised abroad.

263
00:19:01.348 --> 00:19:03.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My parents are both Japanese.

264
00:19:03.142 --> 00:19:05.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? Raised abroad? Where?

265
00:19:05.477 --> 00:19:08.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I mean, so you're not half-Japanese
with that face?

266
00:19:08.730 --> 00:19:10.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t you believe me?

267
00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:11.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t.

268
00:19:16.405 --> 00:19:18.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don’t either.

269
00:19:20.701 --> 00:19:22.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They shouldn’t have given birth to me.

270
00:19:46.935 --> 00:19:49.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
SPEEDY RESULTS INSTRUCTIONS

271
